compound literal
... = (t_...) { .member2 = 0};
>> .member1 = 0, .member2 = 0;

floating point number n can be greater or less than integer n?
ex) (float)1.0 != (int)1
	(float)1.0 == 0.999... or 1.000...

autorepeat (key hold event)
libX11
https://github.com/D-Programming-Deimos/libX11
mlx_key_hook() respond to key release event.
in mlx source file, this function is wrapping hook function of X11 or corresponding API.
change the parameter of hook function from 3(key release) to 2(key press)
then mlx_key_hook() respond to key press event.
mlx_do_key_autorepeaton() function literally does the work.

reversed altitude
before starting transformation, multiply -1 to altitude coordinate to match reversed orientation from 3d space to 2d space(canvas). 
